body:
I review the code of agent, the cause of testcase (#1632 and #1740) failed is in those `Instrucmentation`are : they try to enhance parent method, if we only enhance the method declare, we can solve this problem fundamentally.
example for above problem:
in `org.apache.skywalking.apm.plugin.spring.resttemplate.sync.define.RestTemplateInstrumentation`
we try to enhance 3 methods of class `org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate`,`doExecute`,`handleResponse`,`createRequest`,structure is 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11530760/48339089-3ac6d600-e6a2-11e8-9685-470e618884ab.png)

in pr #1632 and #1740 ,due to limit the enhance scope by declare method ,so all plugins which have this usage will test failure.

so I have a bold attempt ，update these plugins to fit `declared method` by 
`org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate`==>`doExecute`,`handleResponse`
`org.springframework.http.client.support.HttpAccessor`==>`createRequest`

but this make these plugin more complex.

#### so do you have any good solutions?

actually this pr only copy parent annotations to child and copy method.so `@RequestBody` can work well.an example below:
source files:
ParentController.java
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("parent")
public class ParentController {

    @GetMapping("a")
    public String a(Integer b) {
        return "parent-a" + b;
    }
}
```
ChildController.java
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("child")
public class ChildController extends ParentController {

}
```

we use 3 ways to show what byte buddy do to `ChildController`(the result is auto generated by byte buddy by using debugging tool):
# 1.In release version way:
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping({"child"})
public class ChildController extends ParentController {
    public ChildController() {
    }

    public String a(Integer var1) {
        return (String)delegate$a2v8n91.intercept(this, new Object[]{var1}, new ChildController$auxiliary$j6MQIJz8(this, var1), cachedValue$HqrmDcRg$3v0urg0);
    }

  ....
}
``` 

# 2.In this pr way( actually this also doesn't work in spring(request parm binding failed) ,if parmeter is `@RequestBody` no problem):
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping({"child"})
public class ChildController extends ParentController {
    public ChildController() {
    }

    @RequestMapping(
        name = "",
        value = {"a"},
        path = {},
        method = {},
        params = {},
        headers = {},
        consumes = {},
        produces = {}
    )
    public String a(Integer var1) {
        return (String)delegate$a2v8n91.intercept(this, new Object[]{var1}, new ChildController$auxiliary$j6MQIJz8(this, var1), cachedValue$HqrmDcRg$3v0urg0);
    }

  ....
```

# 3.In #1632 and #1740 way
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping({"child"})
public class ChildController extends ParentController {
    public ChildController() {
    }
}
```
so the third is most correct for source file.that the reason I want to only  enhance the declared method.😄
